(4, 'Ridha Fachrizal', 'ridha.fachrizal@gmail.com', NULL, '$2y$10$e63A.wCOZGNs3dOstOIT0OBn8wdm7v4yr1CoCqfjfUKdz5aBTHH.a', '1637756986.jpg', '6.5', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ridha-fachrizal/', 5, NULL, 'Education Consultant | Education & Career Guidance Enthusiast', '<span lang=\"EN-US\">An education consultant at Schoters with more than seven years of experience in the education sector as a teacher, education\r\nconsultant, vice principal, head of learning house, and volunteer teacher.&nbsp;</span><span>Have a special interest in Career Education, Guidance, and Development for adolescents and young adults.</span>', '<p><b>Bachelor of Humanities (07/2014—07/2018)<br></b><i>Universitas Indonesia<br></i>Majored in Arabic Studies with an interest in education in Arab countries. Graduated with cum laude degree.&nbsp; Research grant recipient from International Index Publication for Student Thesis Grant (Hibah PITTA) 2018, Universitas Indonesia. Awarded a full scholarship from Bright Scholarship, Baitul Maal Bank Rakyat Indonesia Foundation, and partial scholarship from Cendekia Scholarship, National Zakat Agency (BAZNAS). Former Head of Student Regeneration and Characters Development Department, Student Council of the Faculty of Humanities.</p>', '<div>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n  \r\n  <p><b>Education Consultant&nbsp;(11/2020—Present)<br></b><i>PT\r\n  Partner Impian Milenial (Schoters)<br></i>Guide\r\n  the students in choosing study programs, universities, and scholarships.\r\n  Assist them in writing essays by developing their interests, motivations as\r\n  well as goals and preparing the documents needed. Obtain a 99.09% of\r\n  satisfaction rate from the students. Help the students (undergraduate and master\'s degree) to get scholarships and universities in United Kingdom, Netherlands, Japan, Belgium, Turkey, and Taiwan, so far.<br><b>&nbsp;<br></b><b>Class Coordinator of Data Science Class\r\n  (07/2020—01/2021)<br></b><i>PT\r\n  Rakamin Kolektif Madani (Rakamin Academy)<br></i>Ensured\r\n  the teaching material suitable with the curriculum for people who seek to\r\n  change careers (beginner to intermediate level). Facilitated and evaluated\r\n  the teaching-learning process. Obtained satisfaction rate in the ratio 90—95%\r\n  and managed to help the students get 84.8 out of 100 on average.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><b>Vice Principal of Student Affairs and\r\n  Indonesian Language Teacher&nbsp;(07/2018—07/2020)<br></b><i>SMK\r\n  Galang Farmasia (Vocational High School)<br></i><b>As Vice Principal of Student Affairs<br></b>Designed\r\n  programs, such as extra- and co-curricular activities as well as career and\r\n  job preparation training programs, to support the curriculum and the school\r\n  vision. Prepared and administrated documents for the school accreditation in\r\n  the standard of graduate competencies. Succeeded to help 10% of student\r\n  admitted to the state university in Indonesia and 90% of student got their\r\n  jobs after graduate. Increased 9 points on the school accreditation.<br><b>As Indonesian Language Teacher<br></b>Designed\r\nthe learning activities that suitable for the curriculum and the school vision.\r\nFacilitated and evaluated the teaching-learning process. Obtained to increase\r\nthe school’s national examination score from 68.4 (2018) to 79.75 (2019) on\r\naverage. Awarded as The Best Teacher of The Year 2019 from the school.</p>\r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n</div>', '<p><b>The Best Teacher of The Year (07/2019)<br></b>Awarded\r\n  by the Principal of SMK Galang Farmasia in the annual end-year teacher meeting.<br></p><span><b>Cum Laude (08/2018)<br></b></span><p>Awarded by Universitas Indonesia for completion of the Undergraduate Program with GPA 3.59 out of 4.00.</p><p><b>Research Grant Recipient (01/2018—08/2018)<br></b>Received\r\n  a research grant called International Index Publication for Student Thesis\r\n  Grant (Hibah PITTA) 2018, Universitas Indonesia with the proposal titled “Traces\r\n  of The Turkish Empire in The History of Islamic Culture: Seljuk Sultanate,\r\n  Mamluk Sultanate, and Ottoman Empire”.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Cendekia Scholarship (03/2018—09/2018)<br></b>Awarded\r\n  a national-scale partially-funded scholarship for a semester from National\r\n  Zakat Agency (BAZNAS). Aimed to help senior undergraduate students that had been\r\n  writing thesis by giving monthly allowance.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Bright Scholarship&nbsp;(08/2016—07/2018)<br></b>Awarded\r\n  a national-scale fully-funded scholarship for two years from Baitul Maal Bank\r\n  Rakyat Indonesia Foundation. Aimed to build social-Islamic activists by making\r\n  some social activities.</p>\r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  <p><o:p></o:p></p>', 'https://calendly.com/ridha-fachrizal/mentoring-quarter-life-projects', NULL, NULL, '2021-11-24 00:15:39', '2022-01-31 06:50:27'),
