(11, 'Marcel Siswanto', 'marcelsisto@gmail.com', NULL, '$2y$10$in.uY/hESSOVyVeHaXJ5AO7nLKbI4iAZjIi5mIM7RUBkJnLu/M4Ti', '1637748891.jpg', '0', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/marcelsiswanto/', 0, '-', 'XL Axiata Future Leaders Batch 10 | College Life Optimization Advisor', '<span>Studied as Actuarial and Applied Mathematics Student with extra leadership activities in Universitas Pelita Harapan, Marcel has proven his life principles named VASA (Value, Awareness, Solution, and Action) have given a change for him and surrounding.&nbsp;</span><span>Marcel has now become XL Axiata Future Leaders Batch 10 Awardee with acceptance rate 0.46%, which is a prestigious global leadership program by PT XL Axiata Tbk.</span><span><br></span><br><span>Starting from his desire to make an impact at the age of 17, Marcel is committed to joining several volunteer activities and non-profit organizations. In addition to his awareness of global issues, he is also active in implementing his knowledge through internships.</span><br><br><span>Marcel proved that he could apply the \"walk the talk\" principle to his life. He was named the 2030 Community of Practice (CoP) Youth and SDGs through his actions in voicing the voices of young people about the environment issues in Indonesia. He motivates, encourages, and empowers fellow young people to start a small action.</span><br><br><span>Marcel also had the opportunity to become a servant leader through his position as Vice President of Majelis Perwakilan Mahasiswa Universitas Pelita Harapan 2021/2022. He is also active in off-campus activities by becoming the Director of Research and Development at IYOIN LC Jakarta. The opportunity to lead makes him a person who is more willing to learn, share, and influence. Marcel has a high desire to cultivate leadership potential in the people he leads with a standard of excellence.</span>', '<h5><b>Universitas Pelita Harapan</b></h5><h6><i>Candidate for Bachelor of Actuarial and Applied Mathematics, Business Mathematics</i></h6><ul><li><b>Courses:</b> Financial Mathematics, Scientific Software, Leadership &amp; Entrepreneurship, Elementary Statistics, Algorithm and Programming, etc<br></li><li><b>Activities:</b> Vice President of Student Representative Board at UPH, Head of Computational Science Club at UPH, Director of Research and Development at IYOIN LC Jakarta, Speaker of \"Life at Math UPH\" Talk Show by Infinitics 5, etc</li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b>Certifications: </b>A10 Financial Mathematics by Society of Actuaries of Indonesia (score: 96.67), Data Science in Finance: Credit Risk Analysis by DQLab, Project Data Analysis for B2B Retail: Customer Analytics Report, etc</p></li></ul>', '<h5><b>Data Science Trainer Assistant</b></h5><h6><i>Xeratic | Jul 2020</i></h6><h6><i><br></i></h6><h5><b>Research/Content</b></h5><h6><i>Ayo Ke Taman | Jul 2020 - Sep 2020</i></h6><h6><i><br></i></h6><h5><b>Algorithm and Programming Assistant Lecturer</b></h5><h6><i>Universitas Pelita Harapan | Aug 2021 - Present</i></h6>', '<span>● UPH Gold Academic Achievement Scholarship</span><br><span>● XL Axiata Future Leaders Batch 10 Awardee</span><br><span>● Winner of Startup Weekend Competition Batch II</span><br><span>● 2nd Runner Up of SISEC 2021: Business Case Competition \"Environment Potential Optimization\"</span><br><span>● Top 5 of Collegacy Business Case Competition</span><br><span>● 1st Runner Up of Essay Competition by Kejar Mimpi</span><p>● 1st Runner Up of Most Outstanding Student<br>● 1st Runner Up of Bahasa Indonesia Debate Competition<br>● 2nd Runner Up of Industrial Engineering Competition<br></p>', 'https://calendly.com/marcelsiswanto/mentoring-quarter-life-projects', NULL, NULL, '2021-11-24 02:25:01', '2021-11-24 19:29:48'),
